snippet.textDisplay: I feel like the "best" route to go on if you have to make a new Ghostbusters is a tv series. Make the business a larger organization, update and streamline all the tech to properly show the passage of time, and put more emphasis on the mythology background fluff that the original films came up with. You can't match the chemistry and humor of the original cast, so don't bother. Have the main draw of the series be the ghosts and paranormal situations, with the cast figuring out how to deal with them. Make it almost like Star Trek and Starfleet, with a large ensemble cast traveling around and keeping the peace. I'm sure you could work some humor in there if you wanted to as well.

snippet.textDisplay:
All of the actors were top of the range saturday night live commedians, at the prime of their careers. The main 3 were also very experienced comedy actors becasue of things like stripes and others movies.

Saying all that, Ghostbusters sucked although looking at it now, it is much better than most sequels (that shows how bad sequels became in later years, not how good ghost-busters 2 is as a sequel) Ghostbusters 2016 was a movie for little girls between the age of about 6 and 12 so that was not really a ghostbusters movie.

But this has potential becasue it does seem to be aimed in the right direction. It has the right air of fright in it (Riteman said that he wants to make a movie to scare the pants off kids and keep it funny - which is a good idea) and if they get all of the living original cast back to do more than just cameo's but to be their actual original characters, this movie may actually be the hit that we wanted from Terminator Dark fate.
